h2.heading.heading--secondary#primary Primary button

p.paragraph.
  A buttons triggers an action to the page or an object. An additional icon can be added.

+example('/components/demos/button-primary.html')

.toggle
  .toggle__button(data-info, data-target='#code-1')
    +svg('source', ['icon', 'toggle__icon'])
    span See code
  .toggle__content#code-1
    .tab-panel(data-tab, data-tab-default='html')
      .tab-panel__header
        .tab-panel__header__tabs
          .tab-panel__header__tab(data-tab-toggle='html') HTML
          .tab-panel__header__tab(data-tab-toggle='css') CSS
      .tab-panel__content
        .tab-panel__content__tab(data-tab-content='html')
          ul.checklist
            li.checklist__item
              +svg('checkmark', ['checklist__item__icon', 'icon'])
              .checklist__item__content.
                Prevent whitespace at the start and the end
                of the button. It will add some additional spacing
                between the icon and the button.

          .tab-panel__content__tab__fullwidth-content
            .highlight: pre.highlight__listing.hljs: code.js
              include:highlightcode ./snippets/button-primary.jade

        .tab-panel__content__tab(data-tab-content='css')

          p.paragraph.
            Use the CSS classes mentioned in the HTML tab
            as mixins.

h3.heading.heading--tertiary UX Checklist

ul.checklist
  li.checklist__item
    +svg('checkmark', ['checklist__item__icon', 'icon'])
    .checklist__item__content.
      Icon only buttons are usually hard to understand. Do not use withouth proper testing.

